1 unit(s) Onion
2 unit(s) Baguette
50 grams Grated Cheese
40 grams Salad Leaves
1 sachet(s) Aioli
250 grams Irish Beef Strips
½ tsp Sugar
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Halve, peel and thinly slice the onion.
Place a pan over medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, 10-12 mins.
Once softened, add ½ tsp sugar and cook until caramelised, 1-2 mins more.
Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once the pan is very hot, sear the beef strips until cooked through, shifting as they colour, 2-3 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.
Meanwhile, halve the baguette down the middle, then pop into the oven to warm through, 2-3 mins.

Spread aioli over the cut sides of the baguette.
Top the baguette bases with caramelised onion, followed by beef strips.
Arrange the cheese on top and, if you like, pop back in the oven until the cheese has melted, 2-3 mins.
Top the cheese with the salad leaves, then finish with the baguette lids.